---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { docsNavigation } from '../../data/docsNavigation';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Neuwerk Firewall Documentation"
  description="Operator-focused documentation for deploying, configuring, running, and integrating the firewall."
>
  <p>
    These docs are organized by what you are trying to do. Start with a tutorial if you are new to
    the product, use a how-to guide when you need a specific outcome, read the explanations to
    understand the model behind the firewall, and use the reference section for exact API and
    schema details.
  </p>

  <h2 id="recommended-structure">How To Use These Docs</h2>
  <p>
    Most operators should begin with <a href="/docs/tutorials/deploy-a-single-node">Deploy A
    Single Node</a> and <a href="/docs/tutorials/create-your-first-policy">Create Your First
    Policy</a>. If you are planning a clustered rollout, continue with <a
    href="/docs/tutorials/build-a-two-node-cluster">Build A Two-Node Cluster</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    The concepts pages describe the control-plane and dataplane split, policy behavior, DNS
    enforcement, TLS inspection, cluster replication, and observability. Those pages are where to
    go when you need to understand why the firewall behaves a certain way before making a change.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose mt-10 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    {docsNavigation.map((section) => (
      <section class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-5">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">{section.title}</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
          {section.title === 'Tutorials' && 'Guided paths for a first deployment, first policy, and first cluster.'}
          {section.title === 'How-To Guides' && 'Task-focused instructions for access, policy authoring, safer rollout, upgrades, integrations, and recovery work.'}
          {section.title === 'Concepts' && 'Conceptual pages that explain firewall behavior, boundaries, tradeoffs, and operational switches.'}
          {section.title === 'Reference' && 'Precise schemas, endpoints, interfaces, and fixed protocol details.'}
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
          {section.items.map((item) => (
            <li>
              <a href={item.href} class="transition-colors hover:text-white">
                {item.label}
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>
    ))}
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
